text: today's recipe is fun for the whole
family it's a ham and cheese chicken
rollup made right in your broiler takes
about 15 minutes start to finish you and
your family are gonna love it seasoned a
thin chicken cutlets with salt and
pepper and then spread some honey
mustard on each cutlet this is going to
add both flavor and hold stuff together
too I have these chicken cutlets already
on an aluminum foil lined rimmed baking
sheet ready for broiling then you just
put a piece of ham I have four total
slices of thin sliced deli ham and then
I cut them in half and then you put one
slice on each cutlet then have 12 slices
of deli cheese it can be switched can be
cheddar can be whatever you want and
then cut those in half so that you have
two small slices per piece there's a
couple of pieces of cheese left over
those go on the top at the end just roll
up your little guys and then place them
seam side down on the baking sheet that
way as they cook they'll sort of come
together
I want to season the outside of these
before I put that last piece of cheese
on but I don't want to touch my salt and
pepper with my dirty chicken hands so
I'm gonna wash my hands first
now season the outside just a little and
then remaining half a slice cheese on
top of each piece get your broiler
preheating and make sure that the rack
is about four inches from the heat
source and then broil them until they're
opaque throughout that'll take about
eight to ten minutes while your chicken
is cooking you can make a little side
dish I'm gonna make couscous with peas I
have a cup of water in this pot just
coming to a boil to that add one package
of frozen peas and then a tablespoon of
butter when the water comes to a boil
add 3/4 of a cup of couscous stir the
couscous in cover it and then turn off
the heat in five minutes it'll be ready
don't those look great golden-brown they
smell fantastic
here's your couscous done and then give
yourself a piece of chicken cheesy
chicken gonna be really delicious you
guys are gonna love it takes about 15
minutes start to finish
